{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_50","type":"agent_message","text":"The root cause is now clear: under `future-defaults-all`, JDI connector construction falls over when `ResourceBundle` tries to lazy-load `com.sun.tools.jdi.resources.jdi` from the JRT filesystem, which is disabled. I’m adding the JDI bundle classes to the metadata so they’re included in the image instead of being loaded from `jrt:/` at runtime."}}
